trailingComments.value:
*
 * TimerModel class sets all needed data for a timer controller to run
 * @example
 * new TimerModel(file)
 *   .then(timer => {
 *     console.log(timer);
 *   });
 * // The TimerModel object
 * TimerModel {
 *  fileName: 'water',
 *  title: 'Water time',
 *  message: '🚰  Drink a glass of water!',
 *  name: 'glass',
 *  endTime: '22:00:00',
 *  bgColor: 'bgBlue',
 *  quantity: 4,
 *  media: {
 *    terminal: false,
 *    computer: false,
 *    phone: true
 *  },
 *  reminders: [
 *    '00:25:24',
 *    '00:25:24',
 *    '00:25:24'
 *  ]
 * }
 *
 *

   * @return {Promise<TimerModel|Error>} TimerModel object with all data on the JSON, plus it's
